President Biden has declared a major disaster in the State of Colorado due to severe storms, flooding, and tornadoes that occurred from June 8 to June 23, 2023. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Jon K. Huss of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and warranted by additional damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.